Conflicts between fpp3 packages and other packages

Source: R/conflicts.R
fpp3_conflicts.Rd

This function lists all the conflicts between packages in the fpp3 collection and other packages that you have loaded.

fpp3_conflicts()

Value

A list object of class fpp3_conflicts.

Details

Some conflicts are deliberately ignored: intersect, union, setequal, and setdiff from dplyr; and intersect, union, setdiff, and as.difftime from lubridate. These functions make the base equivalents generic, so shouldn't negatively affect any existing code.

Examples

fpp3_conflicts()
#> ── Conflicts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── fpp3_conflicts ──
#> ✖ lubridate::date()       masks base::date()
#> ✖ fabletools::decompose() masks stats::decompose()
#> ✖ dplyr::filter()         masks stats::filter()
#> ✖ tsibble::id()           masks dplyr::id()
#> ✖ tsibble::interval()     masks lubridate::interval()
#> ✖ dplyr::lag()            masks stats::lag()
#> ✖ tsibble::new_interval() masks lubridate::new_interval()
